<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8275] NetworkClient leastLoadedNode selection should consider throttled nodes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8275</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The leastLoadedNode() function is intended to find any available node. It is smart in the sense that it considers the number of inflight requests and reconnect backoff, but it has not been updated to take into account client throttling. If we have an available node which is not throttled, we should use it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
